experience

2018-2019

Spent the year being mentored by an Engineer learning the ends and outs of code. I built hundreds of demo projects to enhance my skills. I assisted in UX/UI consulting for a couple of start ups and small businesses.

{/*_ */}

2019-2020

I worked for a financial institution and took online classes they provided on HTML/CSS and Data Structures. Submitted an art piece made out of HTML/CSS to the Bayonetta 10th Anniversary international contest and came in fourth. I received my "Responsive Web Design" certification from freeCodeCamp on 12/19.

{/*_ */}

2020-2021

Received my certification in "JavaScript Algorithms and Data Structures" on 03/20 from freeCodeCamp. I consulted for two small new apparel business in web design as well as created their logo. I re-branded a cleaning service after initially being hired to make a higher quality version of their logo. I also consulted for them in UI/UX. I created the logo for Clippendales, a mobile dog grooming salon.

{/*_ */}

2021-

Rehired to create the website for Clippendales and deployed it using Wordpress and Hostinger. Also rehired to create the website for Neighborly Cleaning Services. I was commissioned to created the EP cover for an up and coming music group. I was hired to create the logo and brand for a new music label. I was also hired to create the logo for a new valet trash service and waste management company. Received my "Front End Libraries" certification 6/21 from Free Code Camp. I also received my "Certified Cloud Practitioner" from Amazon Web Services 6/21
